  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved potatoes</strong> to a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105797716-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105797716-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105797716-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105797716-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105797716-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p><p>Crush your<strong> garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and remove the skin</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105802145-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105802145-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105802145-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105802145-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105802145-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped chilli</strong>, <strong>crushed garlic</strong>, your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>ground paprika </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Add a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and blitz until you have a coarse paste – this is your <strong>malagueta-style marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629105807026-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629105807026-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629105807026-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629105807026-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629105807026-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> king prawns</strong> with the <strong>malagueta-style marinade</strong> in a bowl, give everything a good mix up and set aside</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1629105811916-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1629105811916-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1629105811916-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1629105811916-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1629105811916-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 15 min, remove them from the oven and add the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Mix everything together and return the tray to the oven for a final 12-15 min or until the sweetcorn has lightly charred and the potatoes are tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1629105817188-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1629105817188-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1629105817188-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1629105817188-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1629105817188-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, thread the <strong>marinated prawns</strong> onto the <strong>soaked skewers</strong></p><p>Once the potatoes are almost done, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> prawn skewers</strong> to the pan with any <strong>remaining malagueta-style marinade</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min on each side or until cooked through – these are your <strong>spicy malagueta-style king prawns</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1629105821340-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1629105821340-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1629105821340-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1629105821340-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1629105821340-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>remaining lemon juice</strong> and <strong>carrot ribbons</strong> in a medium bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> and <strong>charred sweetcorn</strong> to the bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix everything together – this is your <strong>gaucho potato salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1629105826347-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1629105826347-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1629105826347-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1629105826347-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1629105826347-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>gaucho potato salad</strong> with the <strong>spicy malagueta-style king prawns</strong> to the side</p><p>Tear your <strong>coriander</strong> over the top and drizzle over any <strong>remaining malagueta sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
